DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(88)90054-2
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199688900542
AB  - This paper investigates the question of whether it is possible to create a strict Pareto improvement in welfare by a multilateral transfer of income between nations. We show that a strict Pareto improving multilateral transfer exist if and only if a generalized normality condition is violated. For a violation of this condition it is necessary that tariff distortions exist. Conditions for the non-existence of a Pareto improving transfer are also established. For example, a Pareto improving transfer does not exist if all commodities are normal and are net substitutes from a world point of view.
