AB  - Although transactions exposure to foreign exchange risk can be completely hedged in the forward market, the same is not true for economic exposure. We show that in some cases a portfolio of currency options can be constructed which hedges economic exposure, when the firm has ex post production flexibility. In the more general case of uncertainty in multiple exchange rates, however, more elaborate options than those currently available are required to hedge economic risk completely.
